# neofetch

> CLI system information tool that displays information about your system next to an image, your OS logo, or any ASCII file of your choice.
> NOTE: Every launch flag has a config option.

- Pass specific options and values:
`neofetch --option "value" --option "value"`

- Allows you to disable an info line from appearing in the output:
`neofetch --disable infoname`

- Hide/Show Package Manager names . (tiny, on, off):
`neofetch --package_managers on/off`

- Hide/Show OS architecture:
`neofetch --os_arch on/off`

- Enable/Disable CPU brand in output:
`neofetch --cpu_brand on/off`

